W. E. S. DYER, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES. No. 7250. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. Jan. 29, 1940. Conlen, LaBrum & Beechwood and J. Harry LaBrum, all of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellant. J. Cullen Ganey, U. S. Atty., of Philadelphia, Pa., for appellee.

Before BIGGS, CLARK, and JONES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

And now, upon motion of J. Harry LaBrum, Esq., counsel for appellant, it is ordered, adjudged and decreed that the appeal of appellant be and hereby is dismissed. Costs to be paid by appellant.
